    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-06-20T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-06-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="11"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d11">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName> Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Prime Minister <persName corresp="#p_CC2" type="from"
                            >Churchill</persName> to President <persName corresp="#p_RFD1" type="to"
                            >Roosevelt</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d11fn1">Received via War Department channels. <persName
                            corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName> was at Hyde Park, New York, June
                        17–22, 1943. This message was forwarded to him by the White House on June
                        21.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-06-20">June 20,
                            1943</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_FormerNavalPerson1">Former Naval Person</gloss> to President
                        <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName> personal and most secret
                    No. 322. I send you the telegram to <persName corresp="#p_SIV1"
                        >Stalin</persName> in the final form in which it went.</p>
                <p>[Here follows, with minor changes, the message quoted in <persName
                        corresp="#p_CC2">Churchill</persName>’s telegram 310, June 13, 1943. The
                    following changes were made in the portion quoted above: “I and my advisers
                    believe” in place of “I personally believe”; and “if secrecy be desired” in
                    place of “if desired”.]</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
